VarAttributes.CATDESC: Nanoseconds since J2000
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: MMS2 FPI/DIS survey data begin-time; derived from survey packet time.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS epoch plus var
MMS2 FPI/DIS epoch minus var
MMS2 FPI/DIS vector of data-quality indicators at survey-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of zero signifies no quality errors. For non-zero values: Bit-0 = manually flagged interval, Bit-1 = overcounting/saturation effects likely present in skymap, Bit-2 = reported spacecraft potential above 20V, Bit-3 = invalid/unavailable spacecraft potential, Bit-4 = significant (>10%) cold plasma (<10eV) component, Bit-5 = significant (>25%) hot plasma (>30keV) component, Bit-6 = high sonic Mach number (v/vth > 2.5), Bit-7 = low calculated density (n_DIS <= 0.0 cm^-3), Bit-8 = bentPipe magnetic field used instead of srvy l2pre magnetic field, Bit-10 = no internally generated photoelectron correction applied, Bit-11 = compression pipeline error, Bit-12 = spintone calculation error (DBCS only), Bit-13 = significant (>=20%) penetrating radiation, Bit-14 = high MMS3 spintone due to DIS008 anomaly

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS compression lossless/lossy indicator at survey-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI/DIS compression loss indicator, 0=lossless, 1=lossy

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) count at survey-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase counts range over [0000, 5759] cnts.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase angle indicates obs +X-axis aligned with the sun-sensor axis.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) angle at survey-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase angles range over [0, 360) deg.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase angle indicates obs +X-axis aligned with the sun-sensor axis.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion energy spectrum "near" +X_DBCS during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Differential energy flux by energy bin, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over particles whose DBCS flow direction is within 45 degrees (polar and azimuthal) of the +x axis (instrument look angles: 45deg <= theta < 135deg and 135deg <= phi < 225deg).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS ion energy spectrum "near" -X_DBCS during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Differential energy flux by energy bin, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over particles whose DBCS flow direction is within 45 degrees (polar and azimuthal) of the -x axis (instrument look angles: 45deg <= theta < 135deg and phi >= 315deg or phi < 45deg).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS ion energy spectrum "near" +Y_DBCS during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Differential energy flux by energy bin, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over particles whose DBCS flow direction is within 45 degrees (polar and azimuthal) of the +y axis (instrument look angles: 45deg <= theta < 135deg and 225deg <= phi < 315deg).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS ion energy spectrum "near" -Y_DBCS during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Differential energy flux by energy bin, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over particles whose DBCS flow direction is within 45 degrees (polar and azimuthal) of the -y axis (instrument look angles: 45deg <= theta < 135deg and 45deg <= phi < 135deg).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS ion energy spectrum "near" +Z_DBCS during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Differential energy flux by energy bin, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over particles whose DBCS flow direction is within 45 degrees (polar and azimuthal) of the +z axis (instrument look angles: 135deg <= theta < 180deg and 0deg <= phi < 360deg).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS ion energy spectrum "near" -Z_DBCS during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Differential energy flux by energy bin, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over particles whose DBCS flow direction is within 45 degrees (polar and azimuthal) of the -z axis (instrument look angles: 0deg <= theta < 45deg and 0deg <= phi < 360deg).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS omni-directional ion energy spectrum during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Differential energy flux by energy bin, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over all directions (flow or look).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion background energy during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Background differential energy flux by energy bin, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over all directions (flow or look).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion background number density during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Background number density derived via integration of the estimated background differential energy flux.

---> MMS2 FPI/DIS ion number density error during this survey

VarAttributes.FIELDNAM: MMS2 FPI/DIS DBCS bulk v spintone
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Estimated systematic error (positive or negative) in spin-plane bulk velocity (km/s) due to imperfect sensor suite flat-fielding. This can be subtracted from bulk velocity to obtain the corrected velocity vector.

MMS2 FPI/DIS ion bulk-velocity estimated spintone vector in GSE during this survey
VarAttributes.FIELDNAM: MMS2 FPI/DIS GSE bulk v spintone
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Estimated systematic error (positive or negative) in spin-plane bulk velocity (km/s) due to imperfect sensor suite flat-fielding. This can be subtracted from bulk velocity to obtain the corrected velocity vector.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> (no error bars displayed) MMS2 FPI/DIS ion bulk-velocity GSE vector during this survey
---> MMS2 FPI/DIS ion bulk-velocity error vector during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Error can be applied to either DBCS or GSE coordinate system

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion pressure tensor in DBCS during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The 3x3 matrix is represented as: Row1) Pxx Pxy Pxz, Row2) Pyx Pyy Pyz, Row3) Pzx Pzy Pzz. Note that Pij=Pji.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion pressure tensor in GSE during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The 3x3 matrix is represented as: Row1) Pxx Pxy Pxz, Row2) Pyx Pyy Pyz, Row3) Pzx Pzy Pzz. Note that Pij=Pji.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion pressure tensor error during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Error can be applied to either DBCS or GSE coordinate system

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion background pressure during this survey
MMS2 FPI/DIS ion temperature tensor in DBCS during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The 3x3 matrix is represented as: Row1) Txx Txy Txz, Row2) Tyx Tyy Tyz, Row3) Tzx Tzy Tzz. Note that Tij=Tji.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion temperature tensor in GSE during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The 3x3 matrix is represented as: Row1) Txx Txy Txz, Row2) Tyx Tyy Tyz, Row3) Tzx Tzy Tzz. Note that Tij=Tji.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion temperature tensor error during this survey
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Error can be applied to either DBCS or GSE coordinate system

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS fast survey sky-map energies
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Geometric mean of parity 0 and parity 1 energies in the 64-step FPI energy table

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS fast survey sky-map delta energies
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Note that the deltas are provided to indicate that FPI is reporting the energy bin centers. These do not necessarily reflect the energy bandwidth that is sampled by FPI at a given energy step.
